<br>
I have had a couple of marbles rolling around in my head over the past couple of days, and I thought I should let them out.<br>
<br>
Firstlyish, I think all of us are interested in eventually having multiple characters, for various reasons of course, but not least among them, it gives us individually and as a guild, flexibility to get into groups or especially to round out groups (for the guild) as needed.  However, many/most of us will not be likely to have the time to play many characters up to 45-50 anytime soon..... So, I had a thought that we should establish days for helping out 2ndary characters (PLing those folks), as well as helping out new members to the guild (like Myene).<br>
<br>
I can say for certain that its a LOT less fun to be in a guild where you cannot participate in what the guild is up to.  You may find one or two people to hang out with, but its soo much more fun to be with the larger group.  My suggestion is six-fold.<br>
<br>
First, we setup a couple of characters who will be within 25% of lower level characters (for the most part).  For level 6 chars, I think you'd have to be level 8, and that seems a bit restrictive, so I might suggest level 15, e.g. we have a couple of folks who keep a character at/around level 15 who can help to get lower level chars up more quickly.  We'd need a couple more folks at about level 20, then probably at about level 30 and then level 40.  <br>
<br>
Second, we have a night where we ALL play characters, whether its primaries for new members, or twinks for existing members, which fit into one of the bands, (something like 8-15, 16-25, 26-35), and we work on getting those characters up.  <br>
<br>
C, as has been suggested in the past, we need to establish some sort of guild bank for loot to be handed down.  Handed-down equipment is one of the nicer features that we as a guild can and should provide.  Right now, we could use a message board, maintained by the originator, but if we do, I would occassionally suggest moving the original message off to a new board to allow for data updates to not be so burried in old messages that it becomes impossible to find them all.  If we do that, I'd suggest you also post its yellow Con level, and its relevant stats (as well as class restriction if any).<br>
<br>
Fifth, I'd suggest ErictheRed, and any of the rest of us who have decent craftsman post a list of what you can make, its stats and usable classes, and what your cost to guild members is for it.  That way, folks can know that they can get decent equipment inside the guild, and do a comparison against what they might currently have.  I don't think I'd make this a huge list, i.e. post the most effective particular type of studded, or chain, of a particular metal, in your opinion.  Folks would need to know that they could maybe get slightly more or slightly less effective stuff for less or more cost, but you could state that at the top of the board.  I would not make that board something someone could post to, they should contact you in game.<br>
<br>
Having said all of the above, I'll be willing/happy to take on managing the Bank site, if folks would like that.  You'll need to let me know via the board please, what you've got and what its stats and con are.  I'll put it out there for you.  I'll also offer to hold it for the guild if needed, I'll come up with a mule char, but it would mean folks need to drop it off at that mule, as he'd likely be frozen at a particular spot.(likely Gna faste).<br>
<br>
Anyway, let me know what you think.<br>
<br>
Pat - or based on Ayinger's response, is that Rat?<br>
